<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-22"><hi rend="italic">December 22,
                                    1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 19th instant on the subject of the refusal
                            of the Canadian Government to admit citizens of the United States to the
                            privilege of registration of copyright in Canada.</p>
                        <p>I have forwarded copies of this note to the Marquis of Salisbury and to
                            the Governor-General of Canada, and I shall have the honor of addressing
                            a further communication to you on the subject on the receipt of their
                            replies.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>